    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - PRINCIPLES, OPERATION AND SERVICE - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Turn traction control off whenever servicing rear axle/wheel components with the truck on
                        stands. This prevents unexpected firing of modulator valve solenoids.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Before disconnecting ANY electrical circuits in the antilock system, the ignition key must be
                        in the OFF position. If the key is not OFF, the controller will record the open circuit(s) as a
                        fault.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>MODULATOR VALVE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Park the vehicle on a level surface and block the wheels.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the air pressure from all vehicle reservoirs.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Identify and mark or label all air lines and their respective connections on the valve
                    to facilitate ease of installation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect both air lines and the electrical connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the valve from the vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
